  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><ul><li>Supervise daily site operations and coordinate with contractors and subcontractors</li><li><p>Ensure works are executed according to approved drawings, specifications, and schedule</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress and report on site activities</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with consultants, suppliers, and project teams</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety and regulatory requirements</p></li><li><p>Conduct site inspections and resolve technical issues</p></li><li><p>Prepare daily/weekly site reports and documentation</p></li><li><p>Ensure quality control and proper workmanship on site</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Civil Engineering or related field</li><li>At least three years of related working experience in A&A, R&R, General Building Work & Civil Works</li><li>Proficient in construction methods, materials, site safety practices, AutoCAD, Microsoft Office, and design analysis software</li><li>Ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team environment</li><li>Singapore Class 3 driving license and ability to process own vehicles (preferred)</li></ul>",
